==English==
{{wikipedia|tilting at windmills}}

===Etymology===
From a passage in the novel [[w:Don Quixote|Don Quixote]] where the eponymous character tilts at (i.e. [[joust]] at) [[windmill]]s that he has mistaken for giants

===Alternative forms===
* [[fight windmills]]

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=[[tilt]] [[at]] [[windmills]]}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[attack]] [[imaginary]] [[enemies]].
# {{intransitive|idiomatic}}  To go on a [[wild goose chase]]; to [[persistently]] engage in a [[futile]] [[activity]]

